39:53.000 --> 40:00.000
Let's go back to the 6 hats technology and evaluate it from the point of view of possible advantages and disadvantages.

40:00.000 --> 40:08.000
When you were doing this task, you probably noticed that it was difficult for you to identify yourself with this or that hat.

40:08.000 --> 40:13.000
But you did it in writing, and in the situation of working discussion,

40:13.000 --> 40:24.000
it is very often that this excessive unusuality of the form of discussion does not allow this technology to be implemented.

40:24.000 --> 40:30.000
Many managers find it strange that they will wear hats or play some kind of role-playing game.

40:30.000 --> 40:34.000
At the same time, there are undoubted advantages of the technology,

40:34.000 --> 40:39.000
and they are related to the optimization of role-playing roles in the creative group.

40:39.000 --> 40:43.000
Very often, an authoritative leader presses the group,

40:43.000 --> 40:49.000
and as a result, the discussion is reduced to adopting the original strategy of the leader.

40:49.000 --> 40:54.000
Therefore, in order to introduce an element of inequality in the discussion,

40:54.000 --> 41:01.000
in order to be able to express different positions on a particular creative idea,

41:01.000 --> 41:05.000
it is necessary to create some special conditions, special rules,

41:05.000 --> 41:12.000
such as the De Bono method, the six hats, which allow you to relate to ideas from different sides.

41:12.000 --> 41:20.000
On the other hand, you noticed that during the use of the six hats method,

41:20.000 --> 41:23.000
the creative ideas themselves are not generated,

41:23.000 --> 41:29.000
they exist in order to relate to the already existing concepts or ideas.

41:29.000 --> 41:34.000
Therefore, the six hats technology is effective,

41:34.000 --> 41:39.000
but it is effective in discussing strategies and in making management decisions,

41:39.000 --> 41:43.000
and not in generating creative ideas.

41:43.000 --> 41:46.000
We move on to the mental map method.

41:46.000 --> 41:49.000
This is also one of the basic methods of creativity.

41:49.000 --> 41:58.000
It consists of creating an association chain around an axiomatic word, a brand, or an event.

41:59.000 --> 42:03.000
You see on the slide such a map.

42:03.000 --> 42:05.000
The key word is associated with the arrows,

42:05.000 --> 42:10.000
association 1, association 2, association 3, and so on.

42:10.000 --> 42:13.000
In turn, from the association of the first order,

42:13.000 --> 42:18.000
you can build arrows that lead us to the subsequent associations.

42:18.000 --> 42:21.000
What is it for?

42:21.000 --> 42:24.000
In order to create a meaningful field of the brand,

42:24.000 --> 42:27.000
you need to see what it can be associated with,

42:27.000 --> 42:32.000
and based on these associations, come up with a creative idea for a special event.

42:32.000 --> 42:35.000
Task 3. Based on the mental map method,

42:35.000 --> 42:39.000
make a tree of associations with the brand of the Caterpillar clothes.

42:39.000 --> 42:43.000
The recommended time to complete the task is 7 minutes.

42:43.000 --> 42:46.000
Task 3. Based on the mental map method,

42:46.000 --> 42:50.000
make a tree of associations with the brand of the Caterpillar clothes.

42:53.000 --> 42:55.000
We check the results.

42:55.000 --> 42:58.000
You see on the slide a simple scheme.

42:58.000 --> 43:00.000
It can be complicated.

43:00.000 --> 43:03.000
The associations of the second and third order can be introduced.

43:03.000 --> 43:09.000
So, there is Caterpillar, the basic association is a tractor, a working vehicle,

43:09.000 --> 43:14.000
the second association is workers, the third association is a factory and labor.

43:14.000 --> 43:19.000
Later we will see how this associative field can work

43:19.000 --> 43:24.000
in the invention of creative strategies for special events.

43:24.000 --> 43:28.000
The mental map method has its advantages and disadvantages.

43:28.000 --> 43:31.000
The advantages can be attributed to the relative simplicity of the form.

43:31.000 --> 43:35.000
You just draw a scheme on a sheet of paper,

43:36.000 --> 43:41.000
and it makes you think about what the brand is associated with.

43:41.000 --> 43:45.000
Undoubtedly, the mental map method pumps the creator's consciousness,

43:45.000 --> 43:52.000
makes him see all the new possibilities of the brand conceptualization.

43:52.000 --> 43:55.000
But there are also disadvantages.

43:55.000 --> 43:59.000
Warming up is not the very generation of creative ideas.

43:59.000 --> 44:04.000
The mental map method creates good prerequisites for creating an idea.

44:04.000 --> 44:07.000
But it is not the very creation of the idea.

44:07.000 --> 44:11.000
Therefore, having created a mental map of the brand,

44:11.000 --> 44:14.000
you need to switch to other creative methods

44:14.000 --> 44:19.000
in order to create a creative idea.

44:19.000 --> 44:22.000
Another disadvantage of the mental map method

44:22.000 --> 44:27.000
is that when the tree of associations is made,

44:28.000 --> 44:32.000
the association is often owned by the creator himself,

44:32.000 --> 44:35.000
a member of the creative group,

44:35.000 --> 44:38.000
and not the target audience to which the brand is directed.

44:38.000 --> 44:42.000
Therefore, it is very important to supplement this creative strategy

44:42.000 --> 44:48.000
and think about what the brand is associated with.

44:48.000 --> 44:53.000
What are the associations that are authentic for this brand,

44:53.000 --> 44:58.000
and not for the creator, who has some individual features and associations?

44:58.000 --> 45:01.000
We move on to the method of search for the opposite.

45:01.000 --> 45:03.000
It is very simple.

45:03.000 --> 45:06.000
If we were looking for direct associations within the mental map method,

45:06.000 --> 45:11.000
then we will look for the concept of antonyms within the search for the opposite.

45:11.000 --> 45:17.000
And the fourth task of our video training is formulated on the basis of this method.

45:17.000 --> 45:19.000
Task 4.

45:19.000 --> 45:23.000
Come up with a concept for presenting a new collection of Caterpillar clothes

45:23.000 --> 45:26.000
using the technology of reverse associations.

45:26.000 --> 45:31.000
Imagine something that is consonant and opposite to the working aesthetics of Caterpillar

45:31.000 --> 45:36.000
and combine both components in the concept of a special event.

45:36.000 --> 45:40.000
The recommended time for completing the task is 10 minutes.

45:50.000 --> 45:52.000
We check the results.

45:52.000 --> 45:57.000
This is the version that one of the participants of my training suggested.

45:57.000 --> 46:01.000
He suggested organizing a collection show in some pathos place,

46:01.000 --> 46:04.000
for example, in a historical building in the Baroque style,

46:04.000 --> 46:07.000
invite VIP guests from the fashion world,

46:07.000 --> 46:10.000
offer them an evening dress code.

46:10.000 --> 46:15.000
At the same time, the entourage of the building and the image of the guests

46:15.000 --> 46:19.000
will contrast very sharply with the collection shown.

46:19.000 --> 46:22.000
On the one hand, this is a certain risk,

46:22.000 --> 46:26.000
because there is a discrepancy between the target audience

46:26.000 --> 46:31.000
and the core of the target audience of the Caterpillar brand in this case.

46:31.000 --> 46:35.000
But nevertheless, this concept can be productive,

46:35.000 --> 46:39.000
because it combines the opposite,

46:39.000 --> 46:42.000
that is, glamour and anti-glamour,

46:42.000 --> 46:46.000
the working aesthetics and the aesthetics of the social society,

46:46.000 --> 46:48.000
high and low.

46:48.000 --> 46:53.000
And in this regard, such a contrast will be remembered for a long time.

46:53.000 --> 46:57.000
Let's recall the words of the hero Gérard Depardieu from the film

46:57.000 --> 47:00.000
The Hotel. Harmony and contrast create beauty.

47:00.000 --> 47:06.000
There are advantages and disadvantages of the method of opposite associations.

47:06.000 --> 47:09.000
On the one hand, harmony and contrast,

47:09.000 --> 47:12.000
what I was talking about, is always very impressive,

47:12.000 --> 47:14.000
it is remembered by the target audience.

47:14.000 --> 47:19.000
On the other hand, the associative thinking is somewhat more complicated here.

47:19.000 --> 47:23.000
You probably noticed that it is much easier to perform tasks

47:23.000 --> 47:25.000
using the mental cards method.

47:25.000 --> 47:28.000
You are just looking for a direct association,

47:28.000 --> 47:31.000
it happens quite involuntarily.

47:31.000 --> 47:34.000
But when we are looking for something opposite

47:34.000 --> 47:38.000
and combine it with what is already part of the associative field of the brand,

47:38.000 --> 47:41.000
it is a slightly more complicated procedure.

47:41.000 --> 47:44.000
I know from experience that some of my training participants

47:44.000 --> 47:47.000
do not immediately cope with this task.

47:47.000 --> 47:50.000
Therefore, if you did not succeed right away,

47:50.000 --> 47:53.000
but having learned about a good option for this task,

47:53.000 --> 47:57.000
you have some ideas, try to complete the task again.

47:57.000 --> 48:02.000
In any case, this creative method is on par with the mental cards method,

48:02.000 --> 48:07.000
because it involves combining direct and opposite associations with the brand.

48:07.000 --> 48:13.000
The basic disadvantage of this technology, like many others,

48:13.000 --> 48:19.000
is that this technology creates only the prerequisites for creating a creative idea,

48:19.000 --> 48:21.000
not the idea itself.

48:21.000 --> 48:24.000
Unfortunately, creativity is a great mystery,

48:24.000 --> 48:27.000
so we are just trying to introduce some algorithms

48:27.000 --> 48:31.000
to increase the probability of achieving the result.

48:31.000 --> 48:37.000
Nevertheless, we cannot fully measure and prescribe the creative process.

48:37.000 --> 48:40.000
We move on to the morphological analysis technology.

48:40.000 --> 48:44.000
The word is familiar, we know the morphology in philological science,

48:44.000 --> 48:47.000
in the science of words, it studies the structure of words.

48:47.000 --> 48:50.000
There is a morphology of plants that studies the structure of plants.

48:50.000 --> 48:54.000
Special events have their own structure and morphology.

48:54.000 --> 48:59.000
In order to apply the creative technology of morphological analysis,

48:59.000 --> 49:03.000
it is necessary to first decompose the object into components,

49:03.000 --> 49:08.000
to see what the event consists of, what is included in it.

49:08.000 --> 49:10.000
As a rule, these are the same components,

49:10.000 --> 49:15.000
for example, sound, visual series, place where the event takes place,

49:15.000 --> 49:19.000
time when the event takes place, target audience, and so on.

49:19.000 --> 49:24.000
But specific forms of the event, for example, in our case,

49:24.000 --> 49:27.000
this is a show of a new fashion collection,

49:27.000 --> 49:31.000
specific forms of the event have their own specifics

49:31.000 --> 49:34.000
and their own components that are integral.

49:34.000 --> 49:38.000
So we identify these components, then we divide them into parts,

49:38.000 --> 49:45.000
change one or more elements and carry out a new assembly.

49:45.000 --> 49:49.000
And what we get is often an unpredictable option,

49:49.000 --> 49:53.000
but this is creativity, when the expectations of the target audience

49:53.000 --> 49:58.000
are combined with something new, fresh, with what the creator has invented.

49:58.000 --> 50:00.000
Hence our next task.

50:00.000 --> 50:01.000
Task 5.

50:01.000 --> 50:05.000
Come up with a concept for presenting a new collection of Caterpillar clothes

50:05.000 --> 50:08.000
using morphological analysis technology.

50:08.000 --> 50:11.000
Imagine a visual image of the show,

50:11.000 --> 50:15.000
divide it into components, change one of the components

50:15.000 --> 50:18.000
and assemble the image together.

50:18.000 --> 50:22.000
The recommended time to complete the task is 10-15 minutes.

50:32.000 --> 50:34.000
Let's check the results.

50:34.000 --> 50:40.000
In the slide you can see a standard version of the Fashion Pokaza device.

50:40.000 --> 50:47.000
There is a background, which usually has the logo of the clothing company.

50:47.000 --> 50:50.000
There is a podium, or a tongue, as it is called.

50:50.000 --> 50:53.000
The models walk on it from the back.

50:53.000 --> 50:58.000
On the sides, along the podium, there are the first rows of guests.

50:58.000 --> 51:02.000
And at the end of the podium there are fashion photographers.

51:02.000 --> 51:05.000
This is what the show usually consists of.

51:05.000 --> 51:08.000
We can hardly change it,

51:08.000 --> 51:13.000
but we can modify it somehow to make the show more interesting in form.

51:13.000 --> 51:18.000
Here is the solution that was proposed by one of the participants of my training.

51:18.000 --> 51:21.000
We replace the podium with a conveyor,

51:21.000 --> 51:25.000
and the show hall with a hangar or a factory room.

51:25.000 --> 51:27.000
We combine the resulting elements,

51:27.000 --> 51:32.000
and we get a creative concept for a special event,

51:32.000 --> 51:36.000
a Fashion Pokaza, which is transferred to the space of a factory workshop

51:36.000 --> 51:39.000
or some production room.

51:39.000 --> 51:42.000
This also creates a very interesting contrast,

51:42.000 --> 51:47.000
because on the one hand, the world of fashion is, as a rule, a world of glamour,

51:47.000 --> 51:50.000
and there is a certain audience of clothing shows.

51:50.000 --> 51:57.000
On the other hand, this obvious anti-glamour contrasts with the expectations of the audience.

51:57.000 --> 52:02.000
The morphological analysis has its advantages and disadvantages.

52:02.000 --> 52:06.000
The advantage, oddly enough, is in the simplicity of the form.

52:06.000 --> 52:10.000
You can't immediately understand how to do it,

52:10.000 --> 52:15.000
but when a participant of the training heard at least one example,

52:15.000 --> 52:17.000
solved at least one case,

52:17.000 --> 52:26.000
he can usually apply the same technology to create a concept of special events for other brands,

52:26.000 --> 52:31.000
because to decompose the image of a special event into a component that can change something

52:31.000 --> 52:35.000
and put it all together is a rather simple thinking task.

52:35.000 --> 52:40.000
In this regard, you can use this technology in a number of cases

52:40.000 --> 52:43.000
when creating a concept of special events.

52:43.000 --> 52:47.000
And, of course, this technology is very effective,

52:47.000 --> 52:50.000
at least due to the fact that it is effective,

52:50.000 --> 52:56.000
and this is really necessary for the event promotion of the brand.

52:56.000 --> 53:00.000
Nevertheless, the question remains open,

53:00.000 --> 53:03.000
is there an object that we can decompose into a component?

53:03.000 --> 53:12.000
The technology was created as an inventor to create new, non-standard products and solutions.

53:12.000 --> 53:17.000
For special events, the event is certainly not an object,

53:17.000 --> 53:22.000
so we usually deal only with the subject environment

53:22.000 --> 53:28.000
and modulate the visual appearance of the event to a greater extent than its dramaturgy.

53:28.000 --> 53:36.000
In this regard, there are certainly disadvantages and shortcomings of morphological analysis as a creative technology.

53:36.000 --> 53:41.000
We move on to the description of creative technology organized inside.

53:41.000 --> 53:44.000
This is a very interesting and my favorite method.

53:44.000 --> 53:47.000
The fact is that the brand is not in a certain vacuum,

53:47.000 --> 53:52.000
and marketing tasks are also not in the middle of an empty space.

53:52.000 --> 53:57.000
There are collective ideas of the target audience of the brand,

53:57.000 --> 54:02.000
there are social practices that are typical for the brand audience,

54:02.000 --> 54:04.000
and all this needs to be studied.

54:04.000 --> 54:08.000
In order to come up with a creative strategy for a special event

54:08.000 --> 54:11.000
that is authentically promoted by the brand,

54:11.000 --> 54:14.000
you need to plunge into its semantic space.

54:14.000 --> 54:21.000
To do this, you need to use the information sources that are somehow associated with the brand.

54:22.000 --> 54:27.000
Inside is a technology that involves several basic installations.

54:27.000 --> 54:33.000
First, the answer is already in our consciousness, we just have to extract it from there.

54:33.000 --> 54:37.000
In principle, any person, using one or another creative technology,

54:37.000 --> 54:43.000
can create a creative concept of a special event to a certain extent.

54:43.000 --> 54:46.000
Therefore, you need to create the necessary conditions for this.

54:47.000 --> 54:52.000
The second installation is that the information environment that you surround yourself with

54:52.000 --> 54:56.000
can speed up the process of searching for a creative solution.

54:56.000 --> 54:57.000
Task 6.

54:57.000 --> 55:04.000
List as many information sources as possible that reflect the style of the Caterpillar brand.

55:04.000 --> 55:07.000
The recommended time to complete the task is 7 minutes.

55:17.000 --> 55:19.000
Checking the results.

55:19.000 --> 55:25.000
These are the options that could be proposed in application to this task.

55:25.000 --> 55:36.000
You can use various architectural forms for awakening creative ideas,

55:36.000 --> 55:42.000
which are somehow associated with the traditions of the working environment,

55:42.000 --> 55:44.000
industrial production, and so on.

55:44.000 --> 55:48.000
It is necessary to remember that Caterpillar has its own legend,

55:48.000 --> 55:57.000
so it is best to use American or at least foreign visual samples that will help you come up with an idea.

55:57.000 --> 56:03.000
You can use, for example, albums that somehow reflect the Bauhaus style,

56:03.000 --> 56:08.000
or the aesthetics of the architecture of brick factories of the early 20th century.

56:08.000 --> 56:12.000
You can walk along the corresponding streets of Moscow or other cities,

56:12.000 --> 56:17.000
where there are buildings with large windows, brick factory pipes.

56:17.000 --> 56:21.000
In addition, it is necessary to remember that some architectural objects are already modified

56:21.000 --> 56:24.000
and adapted for special events,

56:24.000 --> 56:31.000
so such a walk can be quite productive in terms of organizational tasks.

56:32.000 --> 56:38.000
You can use old photos from industrial and agricultural history, preferably foreign.

56:38.000 --> 56:44.000
You can also try to use information sources that are somehow associated with the Russian Revolution,

56:44.000 --> 56:47.000
with trade unions, and so on,

56:47.000 --> 56:51.000
in order to borrow visual forms, ideas, quotes, and so on.

56:51.000 --> 56:58.000
This is all the information environment that can push you to discover creative ideas.

56:58.000 --> 57:04.000
In addition, you need to remember that the information you collect can be used

57:04.000 --> 57:11.000
for the design of special events, for printing products, for the production of invitations,

57:11.000 --> 57:18.000
for interesting options for finding music that is authentic to this event,

57:18.000 --> 57:20.000
visual series, and so on.

57:20.000 --> 57:23.000
There may even be smells and architectural space.

57:23.000 --> 57:29.000
All this will undoubtedly help you create an interesting and memorable event.

57:29.000 --> 57:33.000
As an advantage of the organized insight technology,

57:33.000 --> 57:40.000
it can be called that it provides the creator with a meaningful and stylistic space of the brand.

57:40.000 --> 57:47.000
You surround yourself with objects, sounds, and information sources that are authentic to the brand,

57:47.000 --> 57:55.000
and this allows you to create a strategy that will meet the spirit and expectations of the target audience.

57:55.000 --> 57:59.000
On the other hand, there are also disadvantages.

57:59.000 --> 58:03.000
What if the sea has no weather? What if the idea doesn't come to you?

58:03.000 --> 58:05.000
Like most creative technologies,

58:05.000 --> 58:12.000
the organized insight creative technology is designed to push you to find a creative idea,

58:12.000 --> 58:18.000
but it certainly does not guarantee that the idea will necessarily arise in your mind.

58:18.000 --> 58:28.000
This can be added to the fact that a competent marketer is always trying to find some important information for himself.

58:28.000 --> 58:38.000
He turns to sociological questions, he tries to go through and live the life that his target audience lives.

58:39.000 --> 58:46.000
In order to expand the Caterpillar case, we can give another example from the field of child marketing.

58:46.000 --> 58:51.000
If you are a marketer in a production that produces children's goods,

58:51.000 --> 58:55.000
you may be interested in literature on child psychology,

58:55.000 --> 59:01.000
which relates to that age period that your target audience represents.

59:01.000 --> 59:04.000
You may be interested in the mechanism of decision-making,

59:04.000 --> 59:09.000
about the purchase, how difficult it is for children's subcultures and parents to interact with each other,

59:09.000 --> 59:12.000
who give their children money for certain acquisitions.

59:12.000 --> 59:15.000
You may be interested in teenage magazines,

59:15.000 --> 59:20.000
you may be interested in sociological studies on the child subculture, and so on.

59:20.000 --> 59:26.000
All this information is productive in order to create interesting creative strategies.

59:26.000 --> 59:29.000
And we move on to the next section.

59:29.000 --> 59:32.000
It reflects the benchmarking technology.

59:32.000 --> 59:38.000
Although very often stereotypical thinking is called the opposite of creativity,

59:38.000 --> 59:42.000
nevertheless, creativity is fundamentally different from creativity.

59:42.000 --> 59:45.000
First of all, it is the creator's institutions.

59:45.000 --> 59:52.000
A creative person tries to think by embodying some commandments from above.

59:52.000 --> 59:58.000
We often find this when we read memoirs of artists and writers.

59:59.000 --> 01:00:02.000
He tries to create something fundamentally new.

01:00:02.000 --> 01:00:08.000
As for the creator, he understands that it is difficult to create something fundamentally new,

01:00:08.000 --> 01:00:11.000
so he creates something new based on the old.

01:00:11.000 --> 01:00:17.000
And if there is a shift in the existing stereotypical pattern,

01:00:17.000 --> 01:00:20.000
we are already dealing with creativity.

01:00:20.000 --> 01:00:24.000
This is the right task that every specialist can set for himself.

01:00:24.000 --> 01:00:29.000
Benchmarking is a very popular technology today.

01:00:29.000 --> 01:00:38.000
It involves the transfer of a creative scheme or a management solution from one area to another.

01:00:38.000 --> 01:00:41.000
I will give you an example.

01:00:41.000 --> 01:00:47.000
Let's say you are the manager of a fast-food restaurant,

01:00:47.000 --> 01:00:50.000
and you have problems with logistics,

01:00:50.000 --> 01:00:57.000
how semi-finished products are brought, how they are prepared, how they are distributed to the buyer.

01:00:57.000 --> 01:01:03.000
You look at what industries, what social spheres have similar problems.

01:01:03.000 --> 01:01:09.000
And pay attention to the high-tech logistics scheme of airlines.

01:01:09.000 --> 01:01:15.000
The plane arrives at the airport, and a very quick inspection is carried out,

01:01:16.000 --> 01:01:24.000
the trays with breakfast, dinner, coffee, and so on are placed there very quickly.

01:01:24.000 --> 01:01:28.000
And you can see how the general scheme is implemented.

01:01:28.000 --> 01:01:34.000
When you bring this management solution scheme to some basic parameters,

01:01:34.000 --> 01:01:43.000
you can try to replace the word airport with the word catering service,

01:01:43.000 --> 01:01:46.000
or salon with the word restaurant,

01:01:46.000 --> 01:01:52.000
and see if you can use similar techniques in your business.

01:01:52.000 --> 01:01:56.000
Something similar happens in event marketing.

01:01:56.000 --> 01:02:00.000
I am now working on the book "101 Case on event marketing",

01:02:00.000 --> 01:02:03.000
and I conducted a fairly large-scale study,

01:02:03.000 --> 01:02:09.000
monitoring several hundred Russian event companies.

01:02:09.000 --> 01:02:16.000
And I found at some point that almost all creative solutions are similar to each other.

01:02:16.000 --> 01:02:19.000
If we find something that surprises us,

01:02:19.000 --> 01:02:23.000
then by way of obtaining a creative idea,

01:02:23.000 --> 01:02:29.000
it may be similar to another concept of a special event, made for another brand.

01:02:29.000 --> 01:02:34.000
All this is due to the fact that there are not so many creative strategies.

01:02:34.000 --> 01:02:42.000
I suggest you familiarize yourself with some strategies for developing creative ideas for special events.

01:02:42.000 --> 01:02:47.000
By transferring this creative scheme to the situation of your brand,

01:02:47.000 --> 01:02:50.000
you will be able to see how you can implement your tasks.

01:02:50.000 --> 01:02:54.000
The analysis of creative solutions in the Russian event industry showed

01:02:54.000 --> 01:02:58.000
that all ideas can be divided into several types.

01:02:58.000 --> 01:03:04.000
We will consider them, and at the same time we will see how the solutions that we have already received

01:03:04.000 --> 01:03:07.000
within the framework of the Caterpillar case solution

01:03:07.000 --> 01:03:11.000
could be achieved if we used benchmarking technologies.

01:03:11.000 --> 01:03:18.000
As I said, different creative technologies can lead to the same solutions.

01:03:18.000 --> 01:03:21.000
You just need to choose a convenient way for you.

01:03:21.000 --> 01:03:27.000
The first benchmarking option is called an unusual object in a familiar space.

01:03:27.000 --> 01:03:31.000
I have selected one of the recent examples for you.

01:03:31.000 --> 01:03:33.000
This is a beer promotion called Kirin.

01:03:33.000 --> 01:03:39.000
You can see a sumo wrestler in an inflatable suit

01:03:39.000 --> 01:03:45.000
who performs some strange actions by sliding down the stairs on a bicycle.

01:03:45.000 --> 01:03:54.000
Of course, in this case, the emphasis is on the fact that something unusual happens in the familiar space of the urban environment.

01:03:54.000 --> 01:04:00.000
Therefore, both the passer-by and the passer-by immediately pay attention to this.

01:04:00.000 --> 01:04:07.000
It should be said that the beer promotion Kirin used integrated marketing communications.

01:04:07.000 --> 01:04:10.000
A promotional site of the product was created.

01:04:10.000 --> 01:04:15.000
In addition to these creative actions that were carried out on the streets,

01:04:15.000 --> 01:04:24.000
promoters recruited supporters of this brand, creating a club of fun pranks.

01:04:24.000 --> 01:04:28.000
This is also a kind of event promotion of the brand.

01:04:28.000 --> 01:04:35.000
Those people who joined the community formed around the beer site Kirin

01:04:35.000 --> 01:04:44.000
could participate in a flash mob and play a game with someone from the familiar participants of this community.

01:04:44.000 --> 01:04:51.000
Thus, the promotion continued, the information effect was prolonged,

01:04:51.000 --> 01:04:58.000
and the sales figures show that the promotion was not in vain.

01:04:58.000 --> 01:05:01.000
However, it is difficult to establish a correlation here,

01:05:01.000 --> 01:05:06.000
because somewhere in the time period close to the promotion,

01:05:06.000 --> 01:05:11.000
the prices for this beer brand were reduced.

01:05:11.000 --> 01:05:16.000
Therefore, it is very difficult to establish a direct relationship between the promotion and the sales results.

01:05:16.000 --> 01:05:20.000
Nevertheless, this is undoubtedly one of the good creative projects.

01:05:20.000 --> 01:05:24.000
Another case of benchmarking is direct association.

01:05:24.000 --> 01:05:28.000
You remember how we drew mental cards.

01:05:28.000 --> 01:05:37.000
The associations of the first row, which are directly derived from our brand or product,

01:05:37.000 --> 01:05:43.000
are the associations that are most productive in creating the concept of special events.

01:05:43.000 --> 01:05:51.000
In this case, as an example, I bring the briefing of the mortgage department of Delta Bank.

01:05:51.000 --> 01:05:58.000
This event was organized by one of the teachers of the Moscow School of Business, Inna Alekseeva.

01:05:59.000 --> 01:06:06.000
The idea was to have informal communication between the journalists and the top managers of Delta Bank.

01:06:06.000 --> 01:06:12.000
As you know, most press events are quite standard.

01:06:12.000 --> 01:06:17.000
These are speaking heads, the presidium, the moderator, questions, answers.

01:06:17.000 --> 01:06:21.000
In this regard, it is very difficult to find a creative solution.

01:06:21.000 --> 01:06:26.000
In the slide, in the picture, you can see that the event was not very effective.

01:06:26.000 --> 01:06:32.000
But if you include it in the context of a large number of gray and monotonous press events,

01:06:32.000 --> 01:06:35.000
then, undoubtedly, it was creative.

01:06:35.000 --> 01:06:38.000
First of all, everyone was in slippers, in Delta Bank's branded robes.

01:06:38.000 --> 01:06:42.000
Journalists were able to take the Delta slippers with them.

01:06:42.000 --> 01:06:44.000
Cats walked around the office.

01:06:44.000 --> 01:06:47.000
In general, this home atmosphere was recreated.

01:06:47.000 --> 01:06:53.000
Since this is a mortgage department, a direct association was carried out.

01:06:53.000 --> 01:06:56.000
This is an example of a direct association.

01:06:56.000 --> 01:07:05.000
All creative ideas built on the associations Caterpillar, the factory, workers, for example, moving the show to the workshop,

01:07:05.000 --> 01:07:10.000
are applied to the Caterpillar brand, the case we were considering.

01:07:10.000 --> 01:07:14.000
These are all ideas that represent the association of the first order.

01:07:14.000 --> 01:07:17.000
The third type of benchmarking is grotesque.

01:07:17.000 --> 01:07:20.000
The third type of benchmarking is grotesque.

01:07:20.000 --> 01:07:25.000
As an example, I have brought a collective image.

01:07:25.000 --> 01:07:29.000
This is the Paris agency, which belongs to Alexei Svestunov.

01:07:29.000 --> 01:07:37.000
Alexei Svestunov built a whole business on the Russian book of Guinness records and on the setting of records.

01:07:37.000 --> 01:07:45.000
Of course, the record can be artifacted in different ways, and it is not necessarily associated with the holding of a special event.

01:07:45.000 --> 01:07:51.000
But in general, in some cases, an event is attributed to the setting of the record.

01:07:51.000 --> 01:08:01.000
And of course, the record becomes an event if it is properly covered in the press and the information about it is brought to the target audiences.

01:08:01.000 --> 01:08:04.000
Grotesque is used everywhere.

01:08:04.000 --> 01:08:16.000
In the case of fat sumo wrestlers in inflatable suits, which ride around the city on bicycles, this is also a grotesque option.

01:08:16.000 --> 01:08:21.000
It just so happened that in advertising and in promotion technologies, we must be convincing,

01:08:21.000 --> 01:08:30.000
we must use such bright, exaggerated, poster forms of conveying our message in order to be heard.

01:08:30.000 --> 01:08:35.000
We can give an example from the case we have already considered, the Caterpillar.

01:08:35.000 --> 01:08:43.000
For example, if champagne is poured using construction equipment, this is a grotesque option, clearly exaggerated.

01:08:43.000 --> 01:08:53.000
Or if we say that in the future space colonists will choose only Caterpillar, this is also a grotesque promotion option of the brand,

01:08:53.000 --> 01:08:58.000
because it is associated with the revolutionary idea of ​​the victory of some one brand,

01:08:58.000 --> 01:09:04.000
and revolution is always grotesque, it is always something very large-scale, powerful, and so on.

01:09:04.000 --> 01:09:08.000
The next benchmarking option is the allocation of the aspect of everyday life.

01:09:08.000 --> 01:09:13.000
Here, the technology of organized insight helps us a lot.

01:09:13.000 --> 01:09:22.000
I said that it is always necessary to observe your target audiences and record their collective representations and cultural practices.

01:09:22.000 --> 01:09:28.000
As an example of this benchmarking option, the action of the magazine Samaya was chosen.

01:09:28.000 --> 01:09:36.000
You can see on the picture on the slide that about a dozen girls in the subway read the magazine Samaya.

01:09:36.000 --> 01:09:41.000
Naturally, the rest of the passengers pay attention to this.

01:09:41.000 --> 01:09:47.000
On the one hand, this is a bit grotesque, because not all women can read the same magazine,

01:09:47.000 --> 01:09:49.000
the market offers us more variety.

01:09:49.000 --> 01:09:56.000
On the other hand, this, of course, draws attention to itself, and it must be said that the action was successful,

01:09:56.000 --> 01:09:59.000
although it had certain drawbacks.

01:09:59.000 --> 01:10:02.000
It seems that it was authentic to the target audience,

01:10:02.000 --> 01:10:07.000
middle-aged women go to work in the subway and read some kind of women's magazine.

01:10:07.000 --> 01:10:21.000
On the other hand, the promo girls who were used to hold this action did not represent an age group of the target audience.

01:10:21.000 --> 01:10:22.000
They were much younger.

01:10:22.000 --> 01:10:25.000
In this regard, there was some contradiction.

01:10:25.000 --> 01:10:30.000
On the one hand, the promo action itself corresponds to the spirit of the brand,

01:10:30.000 --> 01:10:34.000
and on the other hand, those who represent the brand do not belong to the target group.

01:10:34.000 --> 01:10:41.000
This is a natural obstacle, because we know that mostly young people work in the BTL industry.

01:10:41.000 --> 01:10:46.000
The next benchmarking option is the unification of cultural practices.

01:10:46.000 --> 01:10:52.000
As an example, I gave the musicals of the foreign language school Mr. English.

01:10:52.000 --> 01:10:58.000
This is a case that has already received good publicity in Russian business media.

01:10:58.000 --> 01:11:00.000
The idea is very interesting.

01:11:01.000 --> 01:11:04.000
When we talk about learning a foreign language,

01:11:04.000 --> 01:11:10.000
we can see a classroom, a group that performs some tasks, a textbook, a blackboard or a flip chart.

01:11:10.000 --> 01:11:15.000
We reproduce an educational stereotype in our consciousness.

01:11:15.000 --> 01:11:21.000
But in order to organize a special action that promotes educational institutions,

01:11:21.000 --> 01:11:23.000
you need something more vivid.

01:11:23.000 --> 01:11:28.000
The school leaders found this way for themselves.

01:11:28.000 --> 01:11:37.000
They began to organize musicals in foreign languages and turned it into a separate business.

01:11:37.000 --> 01:11:41.000
A separate promotional site was created for the musicals of the Mr. English school.

01:11:41.000 --> 01:11:43.000
Several musicals have already been staged.

01:11:43.000 --> 01:11:45.000
Target auditions are held.

01:11:45.000 --> 01:11:49.000
Groups are working in which participants are trained.

01:11:49.000 --> 01:11:51.000
This is a very good promotion option,

01:11:51.000 --> 01:11:55.000
because it allows to attract a large enough audience,

01:11:55.000 --> 01:11:59.000
to attract friends of the participants, their parents.

01:11:59.000 --> 01:12:01.000
This is also a loyalty program.

01:12:01.000 --> 01:12:04.000
Therefore, this is a very spectacular and bright option,

01:12:04.000 --> 01:12:08.000
especially applicable to the educational institution.

01:12:08.000 --> 01:12:13.000
If we talk about the example of the Caterpillar case, which was in our decisions,

01:12:13.000 --> 01:12:21.000
then any contrast between various cultural practices, fashion, work, everyday life,

01:12:21.000 --> 01:12:27.000
all creative decisions based on this contrast can be attributed to this type of benchmarking.

01:12:27.000 --> 01:12:32.000
The next benchmarking option is the event potential of the brand.

01:12:32.000 --> 01:12:33.000
This is how it is called.

01:12:33.000 --> 01:12:38.000
The fact is that very often the brand is already included in some social practices,

01:12:38.000 --> 01:12:41.000
which are associated with events and special events.

01:12:41.000 --> 01:12:45.000
As an example, I brought the Sergei Pupynin carriage salon.

01:12:45.000 --> 01:12:49.000
This is a rather interesting and unusual business.

01:12:49.000 --> 01:12:53.000
Carriages for carriage riding are produced.

01:12:53.000 --> 01:12:57.000
They are produced in Poland, but the brand is Russian.

01:12:57.000 --> 01:13:05.000
Sergey Pupynin is the descendant of the dynasty of manufacturers of these carriages for carriage riding.

01:13:06.000 --> 01:13:15.000
As an event promotion, this brand was chosen as a sponsor for the competition on carriage riding.

01:13:15.000 --> 01:13:20.000
In this case, this is one of the most obvious examples

01:13:20.000 --> 01:13:25.000
when a brand already has an event with which it is closely related,

01:13:25.000 --> 01:13:30.000
and the decision to promote it through event marketing is of course asked.

01:13:30.000 --> 01:13:34.000
The example from the Caterpillar case is very simple.

01:13:34.000 --> 01:13:37.000
If it is a fashion show, then it is a fashion show,

01:13:37.000 --> 01:13:39.000
and in this regard, the form has already been found.

01:13:39.000 --> 01:13:42.000
The question is how to make it more attractive and interesting.

01:13:42.000 --> 01:13:48.000
Another way to promote a brand with benchmarking is to sit down with the event.

01:13:48.000 --> 01:13:53.000
Sometimes there are some changes in society,

01:13:53.000 --> 01:13:56.000
or the expected holidays are coming,

01:13:56.000 --> 01:14:02.000
or some important events in political and cultural life are taking place.

01:14:02.000 --> 01:14:07.000
If the brand of this event does not have a clear right holder,

01:14:07.000 --> 01:14:14.000
then you can tie your brand to it using a seasonal or other event conjuncture.

01:14:14.000 --> 01:14:20.000
Many people do this, although this method of promotion is often associated with legal disputes.

01:14:20.000 --> 01:14:27.000
As an example, I gave the corporate event of the company Megatron,

01:14:27.000 --> 01:14:29.000
which was called Megavidinia.

01:14:29.000 --> 01:14:31.000
This is a very large-scale event.

01:14:31.000 --> 01:14:36.000
It was held in Turkey, where the staff was brought to the intensive care unit.

01:14:36.000 --> 01:14:40.000
The professional director, the event's director, worked there.

01:14:40.000 --> 01:14:44.000
You know by the name that Megavidinia is associated with Eurovision,

01:14:44.000 --> 01:14:49.000
but the first part of this word is associated with the company itself, with its name.

01:14:49.000 --> 01:14:53.000
The employees of the company presented themselves as real stars.

01:14:53.000 --> 01:14:59.000
Special groups were created, like rock and pop groups,

01:14:59.000 --> 01:15:06.000
which performed works associated with corporate history

01:15:06.000 --> 01:15:09.000
and the specific activity of the company Megatron.

01:15:09.000 --> 01:15:14.000
As an example, we can give the group Vulcan Strastei.

01:15:14.000 --> 01:15:21.000
You know that Megatron is the owner of the casino Vulcan and the mountain halls.

01:15:22.000 --> 01:15:26.000
In this case, you can refer to the Internet source.

01:15:26.000 --> 01:15:30.000
There is a promotional site of this group, vulcanstrastei.narod.ru.

01:15:30.000 --> 01:15:36.000
A separate team was created, which could be used in other promotion programs,

01:15:36.000 --> 01:15:40.000
combining the internal and external marketing environment of the company.

01:15:40.000 --> 01:15:44.000
As an example of the case Caterpillar,

01:15:44.000 --> 01:15:47.000
you can bring a creative idea,

01:15:47.000 --> 01:15:52.000
tie the show of the new Caterpillar collection to the day of spring and labor.

01:15:52.000 --> 01:15:55.000
The task 7 will be a little longer than the previous one.

01:15:55.000 --> 01:15:58.000
It will take you about 20 minutes to complete it.

